<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t17650710-11">
               <interp inst="t17650710-11" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17650710-11" type="year" value="1765"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17650710-11" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17650710"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17650710-11" type="date" value="17650710"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17650710-11-off48-c87" targOrder="Y" targets="t17650710-11-defend106 t17650710-11-off48 t17650710-11-verdict51"></join>
         
               <p>353. (M.) 
               
                  <persName id="t17650710-11-defend106" type="defendantName">
                     James 
                     Cooper 
                  <interp inst="t17650710-11-defend106" type="surname" value="Cooper"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17650710-11-defend106" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17650710-11-defend106" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t17650710-11-off48" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17650710-11-off48" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17650710-11-off48" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing a linen sheet, value 2 s.
            </rs> the property of 
               
                  <persName id="t17650710-11-victim108" type="victimName">
                     John 
                     Tandey 
                  <interp inst="t17650710-11-victim108" type="surname" value="Tandey"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17650710-11-victim108" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17650710-11-victim108" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17650710-11-off48 t17650710-11-victim108"></join>
                  </persName>
                
            , <rs id="t17650710-11-cd49" type="crimeDate">May 25</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17650710-11-off48 t17650710-11-cd49"></join>. ||</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17650710-11-person109">
                  John 
                  Tandey 
               <interp inst="t17650710-11-person109" type="surname" value="Tandey"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17650710-11-person109" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17650710-11-person109" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live at the sign of <placeName id="t17650710-11-crimeloc50">the Three Mackerels, at Mile-end</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17650710-11-crimeloc50" type="placeName" value="the Three Mackerels, at Mile-end"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17650710-11-crimeloc50" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17650710-11-off48 t17650710-11-crimeloc50"></join>: on the 25th of May, a soldier quartered with me brought the prisoner to lie with him: he went out in the morning to his exercise, and about ten the prisoner came down stairs, and went out: seeing a strange man, we went up, and miss'd a sheet. I went after him, and stop'd him, and in searching him, found my sheet round his body: then he said he had pawned his coat for his reckoning, where he had been drinking, and he took the sheet to pawn, in order to get his coat.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17650710-11-person110">
                  James 
                  Sedgwick 
               <interp inst="t17650710-11-person110" type="surname" value="Sedgwick"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17650710-11-person110" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17650710-11-person110" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am constable: I saw the sheet found, and heard the prisoner acknowledge he took it.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>I went to ease myself, and found the sheet in a ditch.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17650710-11-verdict51" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17650710-11-verdict51" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               Guilty
            </rs>. <rs id="t17650710-11-punish52" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17650710-11-punish52" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17650710-11-defend106 t17650710-11-punish52"></join>
               T
            </rs>.</p>
            </div1>
